 ## Feedback loop
-The widget stores local thumbs-up / needs-work feedback and can export that history. Use those exports as the next SFT and preference-tuning lane for the dedicated Polly chat model.
+The widget now stores the full thread locally on-device and supports three export lanes:
+
+- **Export thread** — raw conversation bundle for audit/replay
+- **Export SFT** — JSONL rows built from user prompt -> assistant reply pairs
+- **Export feedback** — thumbs-up / needs-work preference rows
+
+Use those exports as the next SFT and preference-tuning lane for the dedicated Polly chat model.
+
+To convert downloaded helper thread bundles into repo-native chat rows:
+
+```powershell
+python scripts/ingest_small_business_helper_exports.py `
+  artifacts/mobile_exports/small-business-helper `
+  --out training-data/sft/small_business_helper_mobile.jsonl
+```
+
+Once that helper corpus exists, the default chat-corpus merge path now picks it up automatically:
+
+```powershell
+python scripts/merge_chat_sft_corpus.py
+```
+
+If `training-data/sft/small_business_helper_mobile.jsonl` is present, it is appended to the default merge input set without needing a custom one-off command.
+
+## Multi-model compare mode
+- The settings panel now accepts a comma-separated `Compare models` list.
+- On send, the primary model plus every compare model answer the same user turn.
+- All assistant replies stay in the same thread with lane labels (`PRIMARY`, `COMPARE`, `ERROR`) and model IDs, which makes the export bundle useful for supervised fine-tuning and response comparison.
